.TH _PRINTF 3 "July 2025" "Holberton School" "Custom Library Functions"

.SH NAME
_printf \- produces output according to a format

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.br
int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf()
function produces output according to a format string, similarly to the standard
.BR printf (3)
function.

This function writes its output to the standard output (stdout) and handles the following conversion specifiers:

.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.

.TP
.B %s
Prints a null-terminated string.

.TP
.B %%
Prints a percent sign.

.TP
.B %d, %i
Prints a signed decimal integer.

.PP
Unsupported or unknown format specifiers are printed as-is, prefixed by a percent sign.
Null string arguments are safely printed as
.B "(null)".

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the total number of characters printed (excluding the null byte).  
Returns \-1 on error (e.g., if
.I format
is NULL or an incomplete format is encountered).

.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
_printf("Hello, %s\n", "world");
  Output: Hello, world

_printf("Value: %d\n", 42);
  Output: Value: 42

_printf("Show me a percent: %%%%\n");
  Output: Show me a percent: %
.fi

.SH BUGS
This simplified version does not handle flags, width, precision, or length modifiers.

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Holberton School students as part of the printf group project.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3)
